{
  "texts": [
    "When T ð2Þ is small, as in Fig. 3d, the 2-hyperedges have few nodes in commmon and this makes difficult the nucleation of synchronous clusters.",
    "Consequently, the synchronization onset is abrupt and, as we increase σ (1), the effective frequencies h _ θ i i converge suddenly to their mean value.",
    "Conversely, when T ð2Þ is large, as in Fig. 3g, the 2-hyperedges share multiple nodes, which promotes the formation of synchronous clusters.",
    "The result is that, as σ (1) increases from zero, we find several groups of nodes locked at the same effective frequency.",
    "As σ (1) further increases, these groups smoothly merge together, until the whole system becomes synchronized."
  ]
}